```class Solution {
public:
    int smallestValue(int n) {
        int result = n;
        while (n > 1) {
            int primeFactor = n % 2;
            if (primeFactor == 1) {
                break;
            }
            result -= n / primeFactor;
            n /= primeFactor;
        }
        return result;
    }
};```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
We iterate until n becomes 1, continuously removing prime factors from n and updating the result variable. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because we only need to iterate until n becomes 1. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space to store the result variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs basic arithmetic operations and does not consume significant energy.

